examples.en: 'Sit!' he said, and the dog obeyed him instantly.
We obeyed the regulation that no cars be [should be] parked there.
They obeyed him out of fear rather than respect.
The law sets down that speed limits must be obeyed.
He obeyed the letter of the law.
She looked at him with the hauteur of someone who is accustomed to being instantly obeyed.
We don't want to lose him. At the same time, he needs to realise that company regulations must be obeyed.
